HEADWORD: Piggin
<hw>Pig"gin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot.; cf. Gael.
<ets>pigean</ets>, dim. of <ets>pigeadh</ets>, <ets>pige</ets>, an
earthen jar, pitcher, or pot, Ir. <ets>pigin</ets>, <ets>pighead</ets>,
W. <ets>piccyn</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small wooden pail or tub with an
upright stave for a handle, -- often used as a dipper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piggish</ent>⟦br⟧
